Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.08,0:00:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.77,0:00:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.78,0:00:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's early.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.56,0:00:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you had your coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.39,0:00:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a lot to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.50,0:00:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.69,0:00:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to what's new in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.55,0:00:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,HomeKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.99,0:00:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11, watchOS 4 and tvvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.46,0:00:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,11.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.33,0:00:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a ton of great features
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and enhancements we'd like to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.35,0:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,talk to you today about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.28,0:00:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we will be providing an
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.88,0:00:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,overview of HomeKit as a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.71,0:00:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.72,0:00:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we're going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.17,0:00:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about some of the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.87,0:00:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,updates and enhancements to the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.11,0:00:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,HomeKit framework in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.44,0:01:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Praveen will be sharing some
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.38,0:01:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting news about our
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.83,0:01:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.05,0:01:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The HomeKit framework allows
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.08,0:01:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps to easily set up and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.22,0:01:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,control your HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.15,0:01:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.87,0:01:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,HomeKit provides a central store
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.36,0:01:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for the configuration of your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.75,0:01:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,home, including rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.49,0:01:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories, automations and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.93,0:01:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.70,0:01:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This configuration is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.87,0:01:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,synchronized across all of your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.10,0:01:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,apps and devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.09,0:01:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And HomeKit is deeply integrated
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.31,0:01:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in iOS, Watch OS and TV OS.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.10,0:01:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can control your accessories
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.23,0:01:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and scenes directly with your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.92,0:01:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,voice, using Siri, or using the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.43,0:01:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Home app, you can control all of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.78,0:02:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your accessories from any of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.73,0:02:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,your devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.94,0:02:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And with just a swipe and a tap,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.03,0:02:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you can control your favorite
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.26,0:02:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,scenes and accessories right
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.40,0:02:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from Control Center, and it has
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.09,0:02:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,really never been easier for you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.11,0:02:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to control your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And with an Apple TV or iPad as
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.91,0:02:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,your Home Hub, you can control
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.82,0:02:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your accessories from just about
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.40,0:02:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.69,0:02:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And we are happy to say that in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.51,0:02:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,addition to being a fantastic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.91,0:02:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,speaker, the Home Pod will also
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.16,0:02:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,be added as a Home Hub later
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.87,0:02:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.02,0:02:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And with a compatible home hub,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.15,0:02:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your home can be automated via
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.44,0:02:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,time and event-based triggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.65,0:02:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And with over 70 accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.81,0:02:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,manufacturers, either bringing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories to market or already
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,have accessories on the market,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.56,0:02:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories continues to grow
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.41,0:02:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,month over month.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.51,0:02:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It is super exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.06,0:03:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a number of new features
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.44,0:03:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about in iOS 11 and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.79,0:03:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,today we are going to focus on
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.67,0:03:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,event triggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.10,0:03:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I'm happy to say that we
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.72,0:03:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are introducing New Events, New
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.40,0:03:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Conditions, support for End
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.16,0:03:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Events, and Recurrences.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.51,0:03:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally we are talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.68,0:03:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the enhancement for Mutable
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Events.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.32,0:03:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we dive into what is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,new, I'd like to do a quick
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.20,0:03:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,overview of Event Triggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.43,0:03:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Event Triggers center around
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.83,0:03:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,events.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.67,0:03:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,When an event fires, it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.66,0:03:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,activates a trigger, and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,have one or more events
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.31,0:03:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,associated to an event trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.95,0:03:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We support two different types
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.89,0:03:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of events today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.73,0:04:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The first, when the state of an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.67,0:04:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory changes, such as
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.59,0:04:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,opening of a door, or turning on
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.21,0:04:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.97,0:04:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we support when a device
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.53,0:04:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,enters or leaves a geo region.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.08,0:04:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And when an event fires, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.40,0:04:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,event trigger activates, it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.19,0:04:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,executes one or more scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.76,0:04:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And a scene is comprised of one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.61,0:04:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or more actions, such as
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.04,0:04:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,unlocking my door, or turning on
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.19,0:04:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,my lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.82,0:04:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can gate the execution
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of a scene when a trigger is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.44,0:04:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,activated via conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.35,0:04:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And we support a number of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.89,0:04:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,different types of conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.15,0:04:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,First, based on the current
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.12,0:04:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, based on the current
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.70,0:04:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,state of an accessory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.54,0:04:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And last, based on the relative
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.68,0:05:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,time to significant events, such
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.88,0:05:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as sunrise and sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.71,0:05:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as an example, When we
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.29,0:05:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,arrive home and we open our
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.08,0:05:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,door, and in this case, opening
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.86,0:05:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the door is our event.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.73,0:05:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And after dark, this is our
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.82,0:05:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.90,0:05:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is based on a significant
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.23,0:05:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,event of sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.45,0:05:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to say execute our
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.51,0:05:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,arrive home scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is an event trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.54,0:05:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a number of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements and new features
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.86,0:05:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for event triggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.18,0:05:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The first of which is support
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.21,0:05:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for date-based events, via
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.89,0:05:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,HMCalendarEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.83,0:06:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This provides an improved
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.89,0:06:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,scheduling capability over HM
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.85,0:06:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,timer triggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.24,0:06:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You can now take advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.62,0:06:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all the features of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.58,0:06:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,triggers, such as conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.27,0:06:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and some of the other features
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.18,0:06:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we are going to be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.62,0:06:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And we support dates based on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,year, month, day, and hour
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,minute combination.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.39,0:06:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as an example, let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.32,0:06:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,ahead and create an event
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.59,0:06:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,trigger which executes at 5:30
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.92,0:06:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,p.m. every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.87,0:06:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we are going to create
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.79,0:06:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,our date component.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.70,0:06:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we are going to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.59,0:06:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,set two properties, the hour
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.90,0:06:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,property to 17, indicates 5:00
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.86,0:06:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,p.m. Second, we are going to set
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.38,0:06:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute property to 30, and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.32,0:06:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this indicates 30 minutes after
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.42,0:06:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,5:00 p.m. We then simply create
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.57,0:06:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,our HMCalendarEvent, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.39,0:06:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,specify our recently created
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.38,0:06:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,date component.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.75,0:07:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we have just created an
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.26,0:07:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,event which will fire at 5:30
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.91,0:07:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.41,0:07:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We then simply create our
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.20,0:07:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger, and we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.61,0:07:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to give it a friendly name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.60,0:07:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we are going to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.07,0:07:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,call it Every day at 5:30 p.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.05,0:07:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we specify our
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.35,0:07:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,collection of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, a single event,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.66,0:07:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,our HMCalendarEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.74,0:07:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, in iOS 11, it is that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.23,0:07:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,easy to create event-based
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.56,0:07:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,triggers based on times of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.37,0:07:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,day or specific dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.99,0:07:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We have also added support for
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,significant time events, via
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.99,0:07:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,HMSignificantTimeEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.92,0:07:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This activates on significant
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.27,0:07:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,events, such as sunrise, and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.82,0:07:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.80,0:07:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And we support a relative time
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.73,0:07:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,offset to these significant
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.85,0:07:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,events, both positive and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.28,0:07:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.30,0:08:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this means you can schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.27,0:08:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,events to fire, say one hour
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,after sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.81,0:08:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's go ahead and create
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.52,0:08:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,another event trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.60,0:08:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, we want it to fire at
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.65,0:08:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sunrise every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.05,0:08:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we create our
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.33,0:08:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,HMSignificantTimeEvent, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.56,0:08:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to specify sunrise as
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.59,0:08:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,our significant event.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.88,0:08:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we also specify our offset
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.81,0:08:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to be nil.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.51,0:08:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this indicates that we want
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.04,0:08:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,our event to fire at sunrise,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.73,0:08:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not before, and not after.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.53,0:08:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We then simply create our
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.72,0:08:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger, same as we did
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.52,0:08:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,before, and we specify this time
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.41,0:08:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,our sunrise event as a single
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.40,0:08:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,firing event.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.26,0:08:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also added a convenience
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.73,0:09:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to iOS 11 to allow you to easily
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,create a condition which is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.70,0:09:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,between two significant events,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.45,0:09:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and note, that because these
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.31,0:09:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,take significant events, they
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,support a relative time offset.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.90,0:09:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance, I can create a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,condition which gates the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.69,0:09:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,execution of my scene from say
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.08,0:09:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,one hour after sunset, to one
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.34,0:09:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,hour before sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.90,0:09:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is available on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.14,0:09:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger via predicate for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.91,0:09:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,evaluating trigger occurring
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.49,0:09:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,between significant events.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.44,0:09:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11, we have also added
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.60,0:09:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,support for creating a event
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.08,0:09:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which executes when a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.32,0:09:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic value crosses a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.68,0:09:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,threshold value.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.95,0:09:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for example, we could
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.84,0:09:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,execute when the temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.96,0:09:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,rises above 76 degrees in our
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.23,0:09:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.78,0:10:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We could also execute when the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.86,0:10:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,temperature drops below 68
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.84,0:10:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,degrees in our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.26,0:10:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we could execute
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.17,0:10:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when the temperature is between
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.31,0:10:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,68 and say 76 degrees in our
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.76,0:10:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.98,0:10:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's go ahead and build an
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.86,0:10:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,example.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.78,0:10:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to create an event
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.74,0:10:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,trigger which executes when the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.55,0:10:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,temperature in our home rises
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.89,0:10:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,above 76 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.26,0:10:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To do this, we first create an
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,HMNumberRange.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.67,0:10:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, note, HMNumberRange is what
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.16,0:10:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,specifies our range between a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.52,0:10:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,minimum and maximum value.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.22,0:10:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have provided two
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.06,0:10:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,convenience initializers for you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.79,0:10:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to create a range within a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.00,0:10:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,minimum or a maximum value only.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.71,0:10:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we are providing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.43,0:10:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the minimum value to be 76.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.88,0:10:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And our maximum value in this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.08,0:10:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,case is an arbitrary large
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.81,0:10:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,number, let's say it is positive
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.33,0:10:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.32,0:10:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We then create our HM
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.65,0:10:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Characteristic Threshold Range
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.16,0:10:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Event.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.48,0:10:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And we specify our target
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.49,0:11:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.07,0:11:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, it is a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.39,0:11:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,temperature characteristic,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.43,0:11:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which can be a temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.88,0:11:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,sensor, or it can be a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.39,0:11:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,thermostat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We then simply provide our
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.91,0:11:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,threshold range, which was our
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.46,0:11:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,recently created range of 76
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.74,0:11:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.78,0:11:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We then, as we've done before,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.97,0:11:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,create our HMEventTrigger, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.04,0:11:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,this time, we specify our single
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.95,0:11:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,firing event, which is our
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.88,0:11:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic threshold range
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,event.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.84,0:11:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the state of our homes are
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.33,0:11:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,often tied to whether or not
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.83,0:11:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,users are in or out of the home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.14,0:11:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, I don't like to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.86,0:11:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,run my air conditioning or have
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.54,0:11:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,lights on in my home when no one
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.33,0:11:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.97,0:11:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I am happy to say that in iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,11, this is now supported via
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.40,0:11:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,HMPresenceEvent [applause].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.68,0:11:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It is super cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.91,0:11:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You are going to love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.56,0:12:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We support a number of different
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.22,0:12:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,types of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.37,0:12:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.92,0:12:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.49,0:12:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,First, when the current user,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.86,0:12:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the device that we are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.94,0:12:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about, arrives home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.94,0:12:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, we can also
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.19,0:12:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,support when the current user
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.50,0:12:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,leaves home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these two replace, or don't
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.79,0:12:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,replace, but they augment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.58,0:12:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,HMLocationEvents, but instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.55,0:12:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,tracking a single device, they
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.24,0:12:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,now track a user.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.80,0:12:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also added support for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.29,0:12:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple users of the home, in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.59,0:12:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,fact, all users of the home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, we support when
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.88,0:12:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the last user leaves home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.61,0:12:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now note, this indicates that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.50,0:12:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,your home is now unoccupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.98,0:12:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a good time to do things
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.13,0:12:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,such as turn off the lights,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:12:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,turn down the air conditioning,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.59,0:12:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,even lock the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.10,0:13:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, of course, we
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.93,0:13:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,support when the first user
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.32,0:13:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,arrives home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.73,0:13:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And this indicates that your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.68,0:13:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,home is now occupied, and in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.94,0:13:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this case, it may be good for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.40,0:13:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you to do things like turn down
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.03,0:13:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the air conditioning, turn on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.61,0:13:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,some lights, unlock the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.51,0:13:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's go ahead and build
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.94,0:13:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this last example, where we
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.34,0:13:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,create an event trigger which
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.92,0:13:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,executes when the first user
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.29,0:13:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,arrives home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.42,0:13:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we create our
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.29,0:13:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,HMPresenceEvent, and we are
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,going to specify our presence
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.91,0:13:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,type to be any user at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.42,0:13:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this indicates that we want
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.73,0:13:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,our event to fire when the first
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.53,0:13:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,user arrives home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.38,0:13:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We then, just as we have done
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.82,0:13:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,before, create an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.11,0:13:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger, and we specify
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.89,0:13:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,our single firing event, in this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.45,0:13:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,case, which is our presence
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.39,0:13:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,event.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And you probably know what I am
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.72,0:13:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,going to say, but it really is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.08,0:14:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that easy in iOS 11 to create
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.12,0:14:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,user presence based automations,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.27,0:14:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is super cool, and we are
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.95,0:14:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,super excited for you to try it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.31,0:14:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,out, and provide some enhanced
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.83,0:14:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,features to your client, or your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.37,0:14:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,app users, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.23,0:14:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we didn't stop there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We have also added support for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,user presence conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for example, let's say that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.68,0:14:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,normally we want to execute our
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.99,0:14:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,good morning scene when we wake
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,up, or when the sun rises.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.23,0:14:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't make sense for us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.32,0:14:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to execute this if no one is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.82,0:14:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.59,0:14:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11, you can now gate the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.73,0:14:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,execution of scenes based on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.81,0:14:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,user presence via user presence
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.11,0:14:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.52,0:14:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is available on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.50,0:14:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger via predicate for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.52,0:14:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,evaluating trigger with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.27,0:14:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.67,0:14:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And note that it takes a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.12,0:14:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,presence event.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.52,0:15:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's go ahead and add a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.14,0:15:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,presence condition to our
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.01,0:15:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,previous sunrise event trigger
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.37,0:15:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and take a look at what it looks
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.88,0:15:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,like.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.84,0:15:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we are going to create
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.58,0:15:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our significant time event,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.50,0:15:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which is our sunrise event,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.01,0:15:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,specifying no offset, same as we
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.33,0:15:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.38,0:15:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We then create our
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.11,0:15:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,HMPresenceEvent, again same as
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we did before, specifying any
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.76,0:15:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,user at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.40,0:15:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We then create our condition via
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.03,0:15:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger, predicate for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.36,0:15:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,evaluating trigger with
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.41,0:15:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,presence, and we specify our
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.21,0:15:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,presenceEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.42,0:15:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we create our
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.05,0:15:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.68,0:15:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this time, we are going to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.98,0:15:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,specify our condition as the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.18,0:15:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,predicate for the event trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.21,0:16:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, and now we have just
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.75,0:16:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,created an event trigger which
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.59,0:16:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,will fire every day at sunrise,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.22,0:16:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but will only execute the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.56,0:16:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,associated scenes when there is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.34,0:16:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a user at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.70,0:16:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're like me, we often want
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to execute a trigger, but only
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.93,0:16:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,temporarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.04,0:16:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, when I open my
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.52,0:16:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,patio door at night, I want my
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.85,0:16:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,patio light to turn on, but
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.27,0:16:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,after say 10 minutes, I want my
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.87,0:16:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,patio light to turn off
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.02,0:16:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.47,0:16:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is now possible in iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.02,0:16:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,11 via EndEvents
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.69,0:16:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.75,0:16:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.82,0:16:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,EndEvents are available on
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.94,0:16:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger, and they return
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.73,0:16:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a collection of HMEvents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.23,0:17:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can update the existing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.74,0:17:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,events or EndEvents for an event
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.87,0:17:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,trigger via update end events
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.10,0:17:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with completionHandler.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.05,0:17:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we have added a new event
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.34,0:17:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for EndEvents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.67,0:17:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,HMDurationEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.52,0:17:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This allows you to specify a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,time interval from the trigger's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.06,0:17:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,execution time, at which point
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.41,0:17:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to end the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.16,0:17:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, on a similar note, we often
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.65,0:17:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,want a trigger to execute only
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.60,0:17:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,on certain days of the week, and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.66,0:17:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this is now possible via
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.19,0:17:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Recurrences.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.10,0:17:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Recurrences are available on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger, and they return
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.86,0:17:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an optional collection of date
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.52,0:17:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,components which specify the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.25,0:17:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,days of the week for which the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.79,0:18:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,trigger is active.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.34,0:18:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can update an existing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.26,0:18:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,event trigger with new
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.90,0:18:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,occurrences via Update
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.25,0:18:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Recurrences with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.11,0:18:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,completionHandler.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.38,0:18:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as an example, I like to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.61,0:18:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,get up just a little later on
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.02,0:18:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the weekends, as I'm sure many
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.13,0:18:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.25,0:18:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't want my Good Morning
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.88,0:18:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Scene to automatically execute
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.97,0:18:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,an hour after sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.93,0:18:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, I'd like to use Siri to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.61,0:18:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,go ahead and say, "Good
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.76,0:18:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,morning."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.83,0:18:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go ahead and gate our
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.45,0:18:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,previous sunrise event trigger
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to only execute during the week,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.12,0:18:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday through Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.17,0:18:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To do this, we create our
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.55,0:18:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,HMSignificantTimeEvent, same as
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.83,0:18:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.46,0:18:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we create our collection of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.18,0:18:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,DateComponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.59,0:18:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going to call these
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.62,0:18:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,weekdays, then for each day of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.66,0:18:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the week, Monday through Friday,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.42,0:19:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we create a new DateComponent,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.18,0:19:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and we specify the weekday
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.39,0:19:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,property to be the current day
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.79,0:19:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of the week, then we simply add
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.70,0:19:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this to our weekdays collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.96,0:19:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when we create our
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.57,0:19:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,HmeventTrigger, we specify our
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.67,0:19:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,collection of recurrences, which
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.96,0:19:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,are date components, as
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.68,0:19:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,recurrences are of our
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.53,0:19:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,EventTrigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.32,0:19:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And this allows us to restrict
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.39,0:19:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the execution of event triggers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.37,0:19:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the day of the week.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.51,0:19:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But furthermore, we also
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.32,0:19:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes want to create an
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.59,0:19:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,event trigger which only
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.36,0:19:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,executes once, and then auto
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.34,0:19:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,disables itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.22,0:19:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is now possible via Execute
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.90,0:19:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Once.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example, you may want to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:19:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,create an event trigger that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.10,0:19:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,executes tomorrow at sunset, but
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.82,0:20:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't want it to repeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.64,0:20:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a great feature, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.34,0:20:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,are excited for you to try it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.27,0:20:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.17,0:20:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is available on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.43,0:20:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger via the Execute
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.92,0:20:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Once property, and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.46,0:20:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,update an existing or new event
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.11,0:20:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,trigger to only execute one time
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,via update executeOnce with
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.44,0:20:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,completionHandler.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.84,0:20:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The last, we've heard your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.09,0:20:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback and we understand how
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.10,0:20:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult it currently is to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.77,0:20:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,update existing events on an
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.56,0:20:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,event trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.58,0:20:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were building an app and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.68,0:20:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,updating a single event, you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.18,0:20:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,first had to copy the properties
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.83,0:20:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of that event in your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.15,0:20:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,application, then you had to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.65,0:20:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,allow the user to modify that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.02,0:20:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,event.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.69,0:20:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the user completed their
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.87,0:20:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,changes, you had to create a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.77,0:20:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,brand new HMEvent with the new
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.46,0:20:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,properties then you had to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.82,0:21:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,remove the existing event, via
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.93,0:21:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,removeEvent with
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.91,0:21:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,completionHandler.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.44,0:21:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then add the new event via
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.63,0:21:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,addEvent with completionHandler.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.95,0:21:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a number of steps to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.41,0:21:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,update just one single event.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.32,0:21:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so in iOS 11 we have made it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.30,0:21:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,simpler via a single method
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.53,0:21:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,updateEvents with
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.45,0:21:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,completionHandler.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.91,0:21:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this takes a collection of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.58,0:21:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEvents which represent the new
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.58,0:21:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,events for an event trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.18,0:21:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have also added support
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.19,0:21:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for all defined HMEvents for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.70,0:21:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mutable copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.77,0:21:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.70,0:21:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can now simply take a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.79,0:21:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,mutable copy of an existing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.65,0:21:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,event, make any changes the user
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.56,0:21:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,has requested, and then commit
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.58,0:21:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,those changes via updateOnce
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.71,0:21:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,with completionHandler.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.88,0:21:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go ahead and see an
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.03,0:21:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,example of updating our previous
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.68,0:21:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,sunrise event trigger to execute
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.23,0:21:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,30 minutes after sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.48,0:22:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we get our existing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.27,0:22:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going to-this will return
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.74,0:22:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,an object of type
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.39,0:22:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,HMSignificantTimeEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.20,0:22:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We then simply create a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.04,0:22:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,mutableCopy, which will return
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.02,0:22:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,an object of type
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.78,0:22:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,HMMutableSignificantTimeEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.40,0:22:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We can then update the offset of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.34,0:22:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,our sunrise event, by creating a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.07,0:22:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,new Date Component.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.80,0:22:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We specify the minute property
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.03,0:22:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to 30, to indicated 30 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.52,0:22:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,after the significant event, and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.78,0:22:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,then simply update the offset of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.80,0:22:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,our mutableSunriseEvent to our
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.39,0:22:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,new date component.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.98,0:22:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now note, we haven't actually
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.63,0:22:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,changed our event trigger yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.81,0:22:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It will still execute at
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.02,0:22:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.54,0:22:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So move our event trigger to 30
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.86,0:22:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes after sunrise, we simply
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.18,0:22:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,need to call UpdateEvents, with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.62,0:22:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,completionHandler, providing a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.14,0:22:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,collection of new events.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.39,0:23:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we simply pass our
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.11,0:23:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,single mutableSunriseEvent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.56,0:23:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And now in iOS 11, it is that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.99,0:23:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,easy for your apps to update
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.69,0:23:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,existing events on an
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.26,0:23:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTrigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.06,0:23:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We've covered a tone of new
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.95,0:23:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,topics and enhancements to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.13,0:23:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,HMEventTriggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.90,0:23:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we have added support for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.85,0:23:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,new events, supporting dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.71,0:23:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Significant events,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.96,0:23:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic threshold range,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.20,0:23:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and user presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.05,0:23:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We have added new conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.08,0:23:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,supporting significant time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.62,0:23:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,ranges and user presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.86,0:23:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have added support, excuse
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.78,0:23:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,me, for end events, which allow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.57,0:23:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you to specify temporary event
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.47,0:23:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,triggers which can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.54,0:23:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,auto-deactivate after a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.05,0:23:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,specified amount of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.15,0:24:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We've added support for
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.49,0:24:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,recurrences which allow you to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.09,0:24:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,specify when your event trigger
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.23,0:24:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,will be active and finally, we
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.26,0:24:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,have added support for mutable
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.24,0:24:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,events for all defined event
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.14,0:24:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,types, which makes it easier for
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.99,0:24:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,your applications in iOS 11 to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.05,0:24:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,update existing HMEventTriggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.74,0:24:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, I'd like to hand it off
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.07,0:24:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to Praveen, to give you some
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.78,0:24:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting updates about our
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.15,0:24:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.87,0:24:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Praveen?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.52,0:24:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.07,0:24:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks Matt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.77,0:24:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.95,0:24:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Praveen Chegondi, and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.80,0:24:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I am here to share with you new
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.69,0:24:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,protocol features and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.15,0:24:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements that are in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.61,0:24:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a few exciting topics to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.47,0:24:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.05,0:24:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to be sharing some
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.88,0:25:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,great news about what we are
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.55,0:25:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,doing with the HomeKit accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.74,0:25:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,protocol specification.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.09,0:25:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I am also going to be talking
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.28,0:25:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,about enhancement to the HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.43,0:25:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.98,0:25:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Supportive new accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.04,0:25:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,categories in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.10,0:25:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Addition to the authentication
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.36,0:25:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,process for HomeKit accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.28,0:25:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we will be rounding
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.87,0:25:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,up with improvements to the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.67,0:25:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,self-certification process for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.69,0:25:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,our MFi licensees.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.05,0:25:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start off with a quick
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.43,0:25:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,overview of the HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.00,0:25:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessory Protocol
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.91,0:25:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Specification.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.07,0:25:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The HomeKit Accessory Protocol
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.26,0:25:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Specification describes how a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.08,0:25:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, which is an Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.47,0:25:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,device, communicates with an
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.29,0:26:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory, along with the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.90,0:26:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,security requirements.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.65,0:26:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All sessions between Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.90,0:26:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,devices and accessories over
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.04,0:26:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,HomeKit are end-to-end encrypted
