Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.54,0:28:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,latest updates, as we continue
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.16,0:28:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to introduce new features and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.77,0:28:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements to the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.81,0:28:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Specification.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.42,0:28:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Talking about enhancements.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.05,0:29:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11, we made some great
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.44,0:29:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements to the HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.90,0:29:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessory Protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.11,0:29:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's see how a user with
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.55,0:29:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 10 sets up a HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.36,0:29:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessory, such as a light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.90,0:29:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,These of course on the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.67,0:29:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory, by putting the light
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.51,0:29:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,bulb in the socket, chooses the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.08,0:29:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory from the add accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.85,0:29:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,option in the Home, and scans
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.50,0:29:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the eight digit setup code.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.53,0:29:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In three easy steps, the user is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.27,0:29:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,able to set up a HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.37,0:29:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessory that is simple and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.29,0:29:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,great.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.15,0:29:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of things to note in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.93,0:29:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this process.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.35,0:29:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The accessory must be powered on
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.03,0:29:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,for it to show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.95,0:29:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, the setup code is used
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.99,0:29:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for the initial HomeKit pairing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.33,0:29:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,only, and this is to ensure that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.91,0:29:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you and only you are setting up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.67,0:29:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the accessory.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.90,0:30:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For many accessories that are
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.36,0:30:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,installed in hard to reach
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.83,0:30:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,places, such as a light bulb, or
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.54,0:30:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,have set up codes printed on the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.85,0:30:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,back of the product, it makes it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.17,0:30:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult to scan the setup code
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.44,0:30:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when it is powered on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.69,0:30:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Or even choosing an accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.72,0:30:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when you are setting up multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.90,0:30:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories of the same model
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.47,0:30:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.89,0:30:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11, we are introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.13,0:30:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,enhanced set of process to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.11,0:30:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,further simplify accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.51,0:30:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.34,0:30:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,With the enhanced setup, users
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.61,0:30:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,can now scan the setup code, and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.30,0:30:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,then power on the accessory.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.11,0:30:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To achieve this, we are
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.29,0:30:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancing the setup payload to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.16,0:30:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,include setup ID in addition to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.93,0:30:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the setup code.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.65,0:30:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 uses the setup ID to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.75,0:30:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,start the pairing process with
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.29,0:30:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the accessory when the setup
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.14,0:30:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,code is scanned, and matches to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.03,0:30:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the accessory when it is powered
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.40,0:30:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.96,0:30:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It is that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.30,0:30:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To deliver the enhanced setup
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.02,0:31:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,code, we are now supporting
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.10,0:31:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,scanning of QR codes for setting
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.42,0:31:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,up HomeKit accessories
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.02,0:31:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.77,0:31:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.52,0:31:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The QR code is standards based
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.28,0:31:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and can be as small as 10 by 10
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.81,0:31:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,millimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.00,0:31:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That is pretty small.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.05,0:31:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The small form factor of the QR
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.87,0:31:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,code will help a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.23,0:31:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,manufacturers to put the QR code
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.04,0:31:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on the smaller accessories, and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.13,0:31:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this is really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.93,0:31:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But we didn't stop there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.82,0:31:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We took one step further, and in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.82,0:31:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,addition to supporting QR code,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.35,0:31:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we also added support for NFC
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.87,0:31:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,tags.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.52,0:31:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.08,0:32:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And we are really excited
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.17,0:32:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.85,0:32:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,With NFC tags that are
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.13,0:32:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,programmed with the Enhanced
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.27,0:32:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Setup Code, we can now deliver
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.39,0:32:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,even more seamless user
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.03,0:32:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,experience for setting up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.14,0:32:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.90,0:32:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The user needs to just tap to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.02,0:32:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,pair and it is that simple, and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.23,0:32:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it is fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.78,0:32:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole experience in setting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.05,0:32:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,up accessories in iOS 11 with
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.73,0:32:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the support of QR code or NFC
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.87,0:32:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,tag for HomeKit Accessories is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.63,0:32:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,just fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.04,0:32:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about Bluetooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.19,0:32:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the last few years, we have
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.80,0:32:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,seen an influx of Bluetooth LE
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.95,0:32:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,HomeKit Accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.07,0:32:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is because Bluetooth LE
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.88,0:32:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessories offer a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.25,0:32:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,advantages.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.33,0:32:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They are small, they are
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.43,0:32:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely low power, and many
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.46,0:32:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are battery operated, such as a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.28,0:32:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,contact sensor, motion sensor,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.76,0:32:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and many more, and users use
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.60,0:32:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,these to trigger events when a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.49,0:33:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,certain action takes place.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.96,0:33:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.28,0:33:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's see how Bluetooth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.18,0:33:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications work in iOS 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.57,0:33:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 10, when an accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.50,0:33:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,state changes, it triggers a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.65,0:33:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,state change notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.68,0:33:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The home of apple TV in this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.74,0:33:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,case picks up the state change,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.92,0:33:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and then establishes a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.94,0:33:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,communication, a secure
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.14,0:33:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,communication with the accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.51,0:33:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to determine what state has
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.89,0:33:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,changed, and then triggers the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.23,0:33:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,automation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.30,0:33:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole process results in a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.86,0:33:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,few seconds of latency for the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.91,0:33:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,automation to be executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.21,0:33:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11, we changed the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.52,0:33:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanism completely to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.40,0:33:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,significantly reduce latency,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.14,0:33:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and we are doing this by what we
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.42,0:33:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,call Secure Broadcast Session to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.74,0:33:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,send the notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.28,0:34:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, the iOS controller
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.52,0:34:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,configures the accessory with an
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.98,0:34:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,encryption key, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.13,0:34:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,interested characteristics that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.87,0:34:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,can be included in the secure
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.33,0:34:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,broadcast notifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.46,0:34:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when a characteristic
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.03,0:34:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,changes, the accessory encrypts
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.41,0:34:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the state change, and then sends
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.22,0:34:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a notification to the Home app,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.98,0:34:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which will then immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.73,0:34:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,execute the automation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.63,0:34:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,With this enhancement, we are
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.31,0:34:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing a number of accessories
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.32,0:34:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,where the latency has gone from
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.65,0:34:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a few seconds to under a second
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.28,0:34:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for the events to be triggered.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.40,0:34:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best part about this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.80,0:34:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancement is that you just
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.91,0:34:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,need to upgrade to iOS 11 and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.83,0:34:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,get new form ware for your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.60,0:34:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories to ensure faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.50,0:34:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because you don't need to buy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.48,0:34:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,new products
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.48,0:34:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.95,0:34:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.42,0:34:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And with the new event triggers
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.65,0:35:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Matt talked about earlier, and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.64,0:35:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with secure broadcast
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.27,0:35:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications for Bluetooth LE
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.62,0:35:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories, it's just
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.17,0:35:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible how home automation
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.01,0:35:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to be defined now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.32,0:35:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming to accessory categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.04,0:35:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,HomeKit supports a wide range of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.37,0:35:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory types from sensors, to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.52,0:35:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,cameras and many more.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.23,0:35:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year, we continue to add
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.25,0:35:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,supportive new accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.63,0:35:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.48,0:35:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, in iOS 11, we are now
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.64,0:35:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,adding support for sprinklers
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.06,0:35:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and faucets
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.03,0:35:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.04,0:35:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.05,0:35:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,With the support of sprinklers
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.26,0:35:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in HomeKit, users can now
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.08,0:35:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,control watering the garden by
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.31,0:35:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Siri.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.21,0:35:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhat in a similar accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.92,0:35:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,category type, which is water
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.92,0:35:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,related, let's talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.30,0:36:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,faucets.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.56,0:36:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,For many users, it is a daily
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.14,0:36:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,ritual to turn on the shower,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.23,0:36:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,let the water run, and wait for
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.04,0:36:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the water to turn to the right
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.04,0:36:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,temperature before you get in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.59,0:36:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.87,0:36:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, while having your morning
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.47,0:36:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,cup of coffee, you can let Siri
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.66,0:36:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,know it's bath time, and by the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.04,0:36:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,time you finish your cup of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.03,0:36:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee, the water temperature is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.06,0:36:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,just right to your desired
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.30,0:36:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,setting, and this can be
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.70,0:36:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,achieved with the faucets
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.37,0:36:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory category.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.87,0:36:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty neat
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.52,0:36:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.85,0:36:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.18,0:36:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about authentication
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.66,0:36:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.85,0:36:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At Apple, security and quality
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.27,0:36:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is of utmost importance to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.75,0:36:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Our customers trust that their
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.79,0:36:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories are tested
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.02,0:37:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,thoroughly by MFi licenses and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.26,0:37:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,audited by Apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.81,0:37:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To ensure accessories are
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.68,0:37:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,trusted and self-certified, we
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.06,0:37:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have adopted hardware-based
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.96,0:37:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,authentication.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.80,0:37:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting with iOS 11, we are now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.53,0:37:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,introducing an alternate method
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.77,0:37:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to authenticate HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.80,0:37:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.07,0:37:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, accessories can be
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.00,0:37:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticated by software
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.03,0:37:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.04,0:37:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.06,0:37:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This provides a great option to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.16,0:37:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,enable HomeKit and shipping
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.79,0:37:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories that can be upgraded
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.85,0:37:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to HomeKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.10,0:37:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For our MFi licensees, we will
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.90,0:37:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,be sharing more information
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.78,0:37:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about the implementation later.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.76,0:37:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Continuing on the topic of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.66,0:37:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,accessory quality, we now have
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.99,0:37:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,new and improved process and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.38,0:37:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,tools to help MFi licensees
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.25,0:37:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,access the launch of HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.20,0:37:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.37,0:38:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have automated tools to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.61,0:38:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,test your accessory and continue
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.25,0:38:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to automate more and more test
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.97,0:38:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,cases, and we urge all MFi
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.26,0:38:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,licensees to always get the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.21,0:38:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,latest tools before you begin
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.24,0:38:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,your testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.40,0:38:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we are glad to announce
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.65,0:38:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we now have two Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.00,0:38:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,authorized third-party labs here
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.73,0:38:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States, and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.83,0:38:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,authorizing more third-party
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.47,0:38:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,labs in China, and UK next
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.85,0:38:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,month.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.52,0:38:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.05,0:38:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And this should help a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.88,0:38:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,MFi licensees to launch the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.77,0:38:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.64,0:38:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,To recap the session, this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.24,0:38:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we introduced many compelling
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.52,0:38:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and useful HomeKit features.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.45,0:38:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Matt talked about the great
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.72,0:38:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements to event triggers,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.54,0:38:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and introduced new APS you can
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.44,0:38:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,adopt in your apps to redefine
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.62,0:38:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,home automation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.94,0:38:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I shared news about HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.39,0:38:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessory Protocol
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.18,0:39:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Specifications being made
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.71,0:39:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,available to all developers.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.25,0:39:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And enhanced accessory setup
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.02,0:39:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,process makes it even better
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.78,0:39:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,than what it was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.84,0:39:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,An interruption of secure
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.41,0:39:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,broadcast notifications for
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.82,0:39:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Bluetooth LE accessories will
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.37,0:39:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,make the event triggers go
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.75,0:39:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.23,0:39:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And introduced new accessory
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.88,0:39:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,categories, Sprinklers and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.17,0:39:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Faucets.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.57,0:39:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we provided an
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.89,0:39:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,update on automation tools for
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.90,0:39:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,self-certification and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.39,0:39:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,authorizing third party labs
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.76,0:39:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,around the world to accelerate
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.47,0:39:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the launch of HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.39,0:39:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.05,0:39:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We at Apple are really excited
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.18,0:39:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,about all these features, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.97,0:39:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,can't wait to see what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.27,0:39:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,going to do with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.30,0:39:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of important things
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.95,0:39:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,before we close the session.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.50,0:39:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We have two HomeKit labs for you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.17,0:39:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this week, where you can chat
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.76,0:40:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with a number of HomeKit
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.14,0:40:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,engineers, who will be happy to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.20,0:40:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,answer any questions that you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.50,0:40:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,have with regards to your apps
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.73,0:40:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and/or accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.56,0:40:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We will also be demonstrating
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.03,0:40:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the new features and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.15,0:40:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements that we just talked
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.91,0:40:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about that are introduced in iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.75,0:40:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,11.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.10,0:40:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The first lab is right after
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.11,0:40:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this session in Technology Lab
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.92,0:40:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,J.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.67,0:40:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.48,0:40:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoy the rest of your
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.39,0:40:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.52,0:40:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.06,0:40:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> See you in the lab.
